title: No steps further than "create training dataset" displayed
body:
OS: Ubuntu 18.04.1
DeepLabCut Version: 2.1.8.2
Anaconda env used: GPU

When I want to enter DeepLabCut GUI, i entered the instruction "source activate DLC2""python -m deeplabcut" in the terminal. Something strange happens, no steps further than "create training dataset" displayed. As the figure shows, I'm wondering what's wrong with the project. I didn't do any modificaitons to the initial code.
`Starting GUI...
Gtk-Message: 07:44:04.353: Failed to load module "canberra-gtk-module"

(__main__.py:969398): Gtk-WARNING **: 07:44:17.885: Error loading theme icon 'gtk-edit' for stock: Unable to load image-loading module: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/gdk-pixbuf-2.0/2.10.0/loaders/libpixbufloader-svg.so: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/librsvg-2.so.2: undefined symbol: cairo_tag_end

(__main__.py:969398): Gtk-WARNING **: 07:44:17.914: Error loading theme icon 'gtk-edit' for stock: Unable to load image-loading module: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/gdk-pixbuf-2.0/2.10.0/loaders/libpixbufloader-svg.so: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/librsvg-2.so.2: undefined symbol: cairo_tag_end
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/komiyama/anaconda3/envs/DLC2/lib/python3.7/site-packages/deeplabcut/gui/create_new_project.py", line 330, in create_new_project
    page6 = Train_network(self.parent,self.gui_size,self.cfg)
  File "/home/komiyama/anaconda3/envs/DLC2/lib/python3.7/site-packages/deeplabcut/gui/train_network.py", line 89, in __init__
    display_iters = str(pose_cfg['display_iters'])
TypeError: 'NoneType' object is not subscriptable
`
